At ﬁrst glance, the third folder seems to contain rubbish: various copies of miscellaneous documents which seem only vaguely related with your project. The ﬁrst document is a price-list for medicines, the next ten are extracts from the health care legislation. Still you continue to leaf through the pages and you stumble upon some ﬁnite state diagrams which appear to describe the internet protocol used to communicate with the health insurances. Apparently, the document is a copy from some pages out of a technical speciﬁcation but unfortunately no references to the original are included. Even the release date for this document is missing, so you don’t have the means to verify whether this speciﬁcation is outdated.
You conclude the reading session with the following report:
